    &xml;-related classes and functions




	These classes and functions implement a C++
	API for processing &xml; documents.
	This is a C++ API to
	libxml.




	All of these classes and functions use the UTF-8
	codeset. All text content returned from &xml; documents uses the
	UTF-8 codeset, and all text strings passed to these
	functions must be in UTF-8.


    &xml_parse;
    &xml_readlock;
    &xml_writelock;
    &xml_dtd;
    &xml_escape;



    Writing and parsing YAML documents




	The following classes and templates are obtained by linking with
	-lcxxyaml. These classes and templates are divided
	into two major, and mostly independent, areas:






	    Writing YAML documents.






	    Parsing YAML documents.






	&app; uses
	LibYAML
	to actually parse and write YAML documents,
	exposing a small amount of its API, namely some
	constants and enumerations.


    &yamlwriter;
    &yamlparser;



    GnuTLS classes




	The following GnuTLS classes are obtained by linking with
	-lcxxtls.
	If you're impatient, you can skip ahead and browse some sample code
	that implements TLS in 
	and .



    &gnutls_datum;
    &gnutls_keys;
    &gnutls_certs;
    &gnutls_sessions;




    Libgcrypt classes




	The following classes and templates integrate
	&gcrypt;
	cryptographic primitives into &app;'s class hierarchy.
	These classes are also obtained by linking with
	-lcxxtls option.



    &gcrypt_md;



    &MIME; classes and templates




	&MIME; classes and templates use the generic
	&ns;::headersimpl
	template to construct a &MIME;-encoded document.
	Instantiating either
	&ns;::headersimpl<&ns;::headersbase::lf_endl>
	or the
	&ns;::headersimpl<&ns;::headersbase::crlf_endl>
	controls whether the entire &MIME; entity gets created with
	LF or CRLF newline sequence.


    &mimestructuredcontentheader;
    &mimeencoder;
    &mimeparser;



    HTTP clients and servers




	The following classes implement HTTP for client
	and server applications, including HTTPS, with the
	help of GnuTLS classes
	(which must be linked with -lcxxtls).




	Overview and current status





	      HTTP, and HTTPS
	      with certificate verification.






	      A high-level HTTP user agent implementation,
	      with persistent HTTP connections, if
	      supported by the HTTP server, and a cookie jar.






	      Basic and Digest HTTP schemes implemented.
	      MD5-Sess algorithm is not implemented.






	      Automatic redirection not yet implemented.






    &httpuseragent;
    &httpserver;



    FTP client




	The &ns;::ftp
	implements a full-featured FTP and
	FTP over
	SSL/TLS.



    &ftpclient;


    Accessing SQL databases


      Installing the &app; SQL library



	The 
	LIBCXX
	SQL
	library is a separately-installed module that
	implements classes and templates for accessing
	SQL databases.




	Install this library separately, after
	installing &app; first.



